HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 68
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
TRANSPORTATION: Memorializes Congress to secure federal funding to remove four
closed bridges on United States Highway 90 in St. Tammany Parish
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to secure
3 ten million dollars in funding to be provided to the Louisiana Department of
4 Transportation and Development from the fiscal year 2027 Transportation, Housing,
5 and Urban Development appropriations request for purposes of removing four closed
6 bridges on United States Highway 90 in St. Tammany Parish.
7 WHEREAS, four bridges on United States Highway 90, constructed nearly one
8 hundred years ago, were closed by the Louisiana Department of Transportation and
9 Development in May 2022 due to structural integrity deficiencies; and
10 WHEREAS, these closures resulted in the cutting off of a significant commercial,
11 commuter, and hurricane evacuation corridor to Mississippi for residents of and businesses
12 in St. Tammany, Orleans, and St. Bernard parishes; and
13 WHEREAS, the removal of these unsafe structures would be the first step in the
14 eventual reconnection of the critical segment of United States Highway 90 linking the New
15 Orleans metropolitan area to the state of Mississippi and the eastern gulf coast.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
17 memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to facilitate the
18 future reconstruction of the segment of United States Highway 90 in St. Tammany Parish
19 by taking such actions as are necessary to secure ten million dollars in funding to be
20 provided to the Louisiana Department of Transportation and Development from the fiscal
21 year 2027 Transportation, Housing, and Urban Development appropriations request for
